This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it discusses caching in wireless systems and proposes a model for recommendation-driven user requests. It also touches upon machine learning techniques such as Markovian models and ADMM-based algorithms, which are commonly used in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses recommendation systems, which falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for biasing the recommendation algorithm, which can be considered as a form of optimization, and thus, it may also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
